## §2. 5-axis cross-contribution

- **Q (QUANTUM)**: bivalent ternary complex VQE + E3 ligase pocket geometry; induced proximity ΔΔG calculation; ternary complex (target–linker–E3) geometry critical (cooperativity α factor); CRBN-tri-Trp pocket binding energy quantum-chemical refinement.
- **W (WEAVE)**: bivalent linker scaffold design (PEG / alkyl / rigid spiro); warhead–pomalidomide conjugate synthesis; click chemistry assembly; linker length/flexibility SAR (the "linkerology" problem).
- **V (VIROCAPSID)**: gene therapy non-fit (small molecule paradigm); but mRNA-encoded E3 ligase delivery (engineered CRBN variant) potential niche.
- **RB (RIBOZYME / RNA)**: RIBOTAC RNA degrader cross-link — Disney lab paradigm; RNA-binding small molecule + RNase L recruiter; pre-miRNA cleavage; 5-axis natural fit.
- **NB (NANOBOT)**: PROTAC nano-delivery (LNP / polymeric NP) for cell penetration optimization; PROTAC molecular weight ~800–1200 Da → Lipinski rule-of-5 violation → nano-encapsulation rescue strategy.

